node.text:
I figured the best way to answer this would be to take a deep breath and speak directly from my gut. 
Gratitude is anchor. 
Strength is my core. 
But the pain of having to bury my dad this past week really tested my strength and complicated my gratitude. 
I had no preconceived ideas of how this chat with Oprah would go, other than I was just going to be as present and as authentic as I could for whatever the audience and Oprah needs. 
Just be me. 
But the widest thing hit me when she asked me this question...
and that’s how much I NEEDED THIS. 
The love, care, empathy, laughs, light and strength from her and the 12,000+ people in the arena. 
I came to give. 
But had no idea how much I would actually receive. 
@oprah, a huge mahalo being such a friend and mentor. 
And HAPPY BIRTHDAY!! 🎉🎂🙌🏾 🥃🕺🏽 #TodayIsSuchADay 
#Oprahs2020VisionTour 
Enjoy my FULL CHAT with Oprah in my link up top ☝🏾☝🏾

Ive always had the utmost admiratipn n respect for you as a gifted pro wrestler i may not have liked you....but everyday you showed me ur not judge a book by its cover...to look beyond the cover through the pages...Ur father you grandfather i grew up loving them as a teenager...and now its vome full circle...loves n hugs Rock❤️❤️❤️❤️
To such a wonderful humble man that God has put in this earth! 😇🙏

My condolences. I lost my grandma this past year and that hit me like a rock too. Not you but 😂 But ya pun not intended, It was really hard to get back on my feet let alone even walk. My heart goes out to you and hope you find peace and gain a sense of gratitude again for the blessings you still have 🙏🏽
❤️and I am grateful to YOUR EXISTENCE 💕 @therock 💕😍❤️😘😘😘
Gratitude is key!!! When I get down, I make a list. Sober almost 29 years.
You are such a genuine and amazing person. I love watching your videos and words of wisdom and how to be grateful for life

shortcode_media.title: When @oprah asked me, “what am I now most grateful for today?” •
